-- Japanese Sold Net 721.5 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 2012-03-22T23:54:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-22/japanese-sold-net-721-5-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended March 16 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors sold 721.5 billion yen ($8.7 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 57.8 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 38.8 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 818.1 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 1066.7 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 287.5 billion yen in stocks, and bought 1089.8 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 310.5
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Minh Bui in Tokyo at   mbui@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
